{% extends 'base.jinja' %}

{% block topstatic %}
<link rel='stylesheet' href="{{ url_for('static', filename='home.css') }}">
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<div class='jumbotron jumbotron-fluid bg-transparent bottom-yellow-wave-1 jumbo-nomargin'>
    <div class='main-home-div'>
        <h1 class='text-center'>Starboard</h1>
        <h4 class='text-center'>The most advanced starboard</h4>
        <p class='text-center'>{{ gcount }} servers | {{ mcount }} users</p>
        <div class="justify-content-center align-items-middle bg-transparent text-center">
            <a class='btn mybtn btn-myprimary' href="{{ url_for('servers') }}">Dashboard</a> <a class='btn mybtn btn-mysecondary' href="#">Support Starboard</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class='jumbotron jumbotron-fluid bg-myyellow bottom-dgrey-wave-1'>
    <h2 class='text-center' style="color: black;">Features</h2>
    <div class='container bot-features'>
        <div class="row d-flex justify-content-center align-items-middle bg-transparent">
            <div class='col-md-3 text-center feature-card'>
                <h3>Multiple Starboards</h3>
                Add multiple starboards to your server!
                <br>
                <button type='button' class='btn btn-myprimary feature-button' data-toggle='modal' data-target="#starboardsModal">
                    Read More
                </button>
            </div>
            <div class='col-md-3 text-center feature-card'>
                <h3>Multiple Emojis</h3>
                You can have multiple starboard emojis on each starboard!
                <br>
                <button type='button' class='btn btn-myprimary feature-button' data-toggle='modal' data-target="#emojisModal">
                    Read More
                </button>
            </div>
            <div class='col-md-3 text-center feature-card'>
                <h3>Message Moderation</h3>
                Easily manage starred messages to keep the starboard clean and high quality!
                <br>
                <button type='button' class='btn btn-myprimary feature-button' data-toggle='modal' data-target='#modModal'>
                    Read More
                </button>
            </div>
            <div class='col-md-3 text-center feature-card'>
                <h3>AutoStar Channels</h3>
                Have the bot automatically star messages, so users can star them easily!
                <br>
                <button type='button' class='btn btn-myprimary feature-button' data-toggle='modal' data-target='#autostarModal'>
                    Read More
                </button>
            </div>
            <div class='col-md-3 text-center feature-card'>
                <h3>Leveling and XP</h3>
                Gain XP every minute you receive a star, and work your way up the leaderboard!
                <br>
                <button type='button' class='btn btn-myprimary feature-button' data-toggle='modal' data-target='#xpModal'>
                    Read More
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class='modal fade' id='starboardsModal'>
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered">
        <div class='modal-content bg-dark'>

            <div class='modal-header'>
                <h1>Multiple Starboards</h1>
                <button type='button' class='close' data-dismiss='modal'>×</button>
            </div>

            <div class='modal-body'>
                <p>Unlike most starboards, this bot allows you to have multiple starboards, each with its own configuration. For example, you could have a regular starboard, which requires 3 stars, and a super-starboard, which requires 5 stars.
            </div>

            <div class='modal-footer'>
                <button type='button' class='btn btn-mysecondary' data-dismiss='modal'>Close</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class='modal fade' id='emojisModal'>
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered">
        <div class='modal-content bg-dark'>

            <div class='modal-header'>
                <h1>Multiple Emojis</h1>
                <button type='button' class='close' data-dismiss='modal'>×</button>
            </div>

            <div class='modal-body'>
                <p>Each of your starboards can have multiple "star" emojis on them, normal or custom, giving your users multiple ways to star messages.
            </div>

            <div class='modal-footer'>
                <button type='button' class='btn btn-mysecondary' data-dismiss='modal'>Close</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class='modal fade' id='modModal'>
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered">
        <div class='modal-content bg-dark'>

            <div class='modal-header'>
                <h1>Message Moderation</h1>
                <button type='button' class='close' data-dismiss='modal'>×</button>
            </div>

            <div class='modal-body'>
                <p>Starboard comes with very useful message moderation features, such as trashing, which effectively deletes a message from all starboards, forcing, which sends a message to the starboard regardless of its stars, and freezing, which prevents a message from gaining or loosing stars.</p>
            </div>

            <div class='modal-footer'>
                <button type='button' class='btn btn-mysecondary' data-dismiss='modal'>Close</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class='modal fade' id='autostarModal'>
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered">
        <div class='modal-content bg-dark'>

            <div class='modal-header'>
                <h1>AutoStar Channels</h1>
                <button type='button' class='close' data-dismiss='modal'>×</button>
            </div>

            <div class='modal-body'>
                <p>A unique feature of this starboard is AutoStar channels. These are channels where messages sent will be automatically starred, if they meet the requirments you set. You can set a character limit, wether or not it requires an image, and wether invalid messages are auto-deleted.</p>
            </div>

            <div class='modal-footer'>
                <button type='button' class='btn btn-mysecondary' data-dismiss='modal'>Close</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class='modal fade' id='xpModal'>
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered">
        <div class='modal-content bg-dark'>

            <div class='modal-header'>
                <h1>Leveling and XP</h1>
                <button type='button' class='close' data-dismiss='modal'>×</button>
            </div>

            <div class='modal-body'>
                <p>Most starboard bots simply count the number of stars a user receives. While this works, this encourages things like star-for-star and reaction spamming. This bot takes a different approach. Every minute a user stars another user, that user receives 1 XP. Then, the more XP they gain, the higher their level is, giving servers a spam-free but still fun leaderboard system.</p>
            </div>

            <div class='modal-footer'>
                <button type='button' class='btn btn-mysecondary' data-dismiss='modal'>Close</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}